   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   TWIN-DOCS _ Identical twins Travis and Travan Jasper were born
37 seconds apart. In high school they were co-valedictorians; they
went to the same college, medical school, and residency program,
where they both chose emergency medicine as a specialty. Now they
both teach at Emory University School of Medicine and work in
emergency departments in the Emory system, though never in the same
one at the same time to cut down risky confusion. Their story's
already unusual, but it has an extra component: They're
African-American, working in one of the whitest specialties in
medicine. With pictures of the docs in the ER and out of their
white coats, together. (McKenna, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
WEIGHT-LOSS _ How I took the weight off and kept it off. (Heisler,
Palm Beach Post). 12.
</P>
<P>
   PARENTING _ If you are sick of reading parenting books that are
peppered with lists and advice, Dr. Kyle Pruett has a solution. In
his latest book, Me, Myself and I: How Children Build Their Sense
of Self (Goddard Press, $19.95) Pruett guides parents on how to
shape children from 18 months to 36 months. (Dayton Daily News).
10. SEA-LICE _ A Boynton Beach, Fla., company says it has the
answer to the itchy, red stings of sea lice, hornets, ants and
other native Florida pests. International Ozone's Lands End Oil
deactivates the venom in bites and stings to stop itching and
swelling, according to company representatives. (Palm Beach Post).
10.
</P>
