   DEPRESSION WALK _ Almost every day for the past three months,
someone has stopped Stuart Perry on the road, wanting to talk about
depression. Since May, Perry has walked on back roads from Georgia
to Chicago talking about depression to anyone who would listen. He
began his trek to educate people about the devastating illness and
to give hope about treatment. (Miller, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ANTIOXIDENTS GAIN RESPECT -- An increasing number of people
believe that antioxidants _ certain vitamins, minerals and
plant-based chemicals _ are the key to maintaining health if you
live in a city with high levels of air pollution and other toxic
chemicals. (Kennedy, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes
