forget, Joe Bernal has a special interest in the campaign for the
White House this year. At 72, Bernal can recall when minority
outreach by political candidates consisted of paying a person's
poll tax and, on good days, getting some tamales and beer to wash
down the ignominy of casting a ballot for the status quo. By JAIME
CASTILLO. (For release Sunday, Aug. 1.)
