oldest public ratio station, KPFA-FM in Berkeley, Calif., brought
thousands of protesters to the streets of Berkeley, home of a
University of California campus and site of much 1960s student
revolutionary unrest. By ALAN TURNER.
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-GAS (San Francisco) _ Two environmental groups have gone
to court to try to stop Chevron from selling so-called dirty
gasoline. The plaintiffs are trying to overturn the state Air
Resources Board's decision two weeks ago giving Chevron permission
to sell gasoline that does not meet stringent state clean-air
standards. By The San Francisco Examiner.
