<SLUG> BC-BRITNEY-SPEARS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SPEARS IS ROYALTY AMONG TEENS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By CRAIG MARINE  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   OAKLAND, Calif. _ Britney Spears is the reigning Queen of Teen.
</P>
<P>
   In her music videos, Spears is 17 going on about 28, the
provocative little Lolita with one button too many undone on her
Catholic school uniform, overly made-up and a look in her eyes
that's a bit too knowing.
</P>
<P>
   She's been accused of lying about her age and having plastic
surgery. She's been subjected to all manner of sniping that goes
with instant fame and riches. Her debut album, ``Baby One More
Time,'' has sold 5 million copies with no sign of slowing down. A
concert at the Paramount Theatre in Oakland was sold out Thursday
night.
</P>
<P>
   Spears, who is from Edgewood, La., population 1,200, seems like
the poster child for a packaged teen act, which she may well be.
But in reality, in person, up close, she really is just a kid. Her
forehead has a patch of acne cleverly covered by makeup. She talks
in a soft voice, with an evident Southern drawl. She's amazingly
courteous to the 250 fans lucky enough to be chosen to receive
autographs during her hourlong appearance on stage under the hot
sun. And even she is a bit baffled by the cyclone of fame.
</P>
<P>
   ``This has all happened so fast I haven't even really been able
to catch my breath,'' a smiling Spears said between autographs.
``To tell you the truth, I don't really know what to make of all
this, except that I'm extremely grateful and I certainly realize
how lucky I am.''
</P>
<P>
   But while Spears is down home enough to admit to sweating like a
horse in her tour sponsor's quilted vest, part of her chosen
ensemble, there were some indications that she wasn't quite like
the average 17-year-old _ like when she spoke of missing her
brand-new white Mercedes convertible.
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't been home enough to drive it,'' she sighed. ``Maybe
once the tour's done and I get out of the studio I'll be able to
spend some time behind the wheel.''
</P>
</TEXT>
