<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CLARIFICATION TO STORY SLUGGED ``COX-CHECKS-Y2K''
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A Cox News Service story Thursday said Social Security
Administration benefit checks will be delivered on Dec. 29 in case
the U.S. Postal Service has problems associated with the Y2K
computer bug in the change to the year 2000. In fact, the checks
will be given on Dec. 29 to the Postal Service, which will
distribute them to recipients on Jan. 3, the first Monday of the
new year.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
