<P>
   HINDU TEMPLE-TEXAS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Dirt is turning at the D/FW Hindu Temple Society
complex. Temple society organizers are making room for a community
of Hindus that began with a few families meeting north of Dallas
nearly 20 years ago and now draws more than 1,260 members from
throughout the Metroplex. By TARA DOOLEY. Story will move in ``a''
general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TV-PERKINS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ Critics have complained about the lack of
black- and Hispanic-cast shows this TV season. Now CBS has
announced one, supervised by superproducer Steven Bochco. But what
does it say that to get on the air, a black drama needs a white
producer? By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
