   UNDATED _ Finally, there's a Lincoln sedan that ought to appeal
to upscale consumers whose hair is just beginning to turn gray. The
1999 LS, a sporty performance sedan in the same vein as the Lexus
GS 400, represents a departure from Lincoln automobiles of the
past, and should give Ford Motor Co. and its Lincoln-Mercury
Division dealers some hope for the future. By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS
III. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
