<P>
   COMPUTERS-BOMBAY-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ A reader asks Dr. Bombay: ``It was with great
excitement that I let the cable modem people in. I had taken a day
off work and convinced my wife that the $100 installation fee was a
bargain. Anyway, they couldn't install it because my apartment had
the wrong kind of cable. They would need to set up an appointment
with `construction' and then another one with themselves. Oh, yes,
and the fee would go up $75. Faced with almost double the
installation and two more days of missed work, I told them to put
everything back the way it was, and I'd just live with 56K. Was I
being scammed, or did I cut my nose off?'' By DR. EMILIO BOMBAY.
Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
