   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ One of the most annoying aspects of the ongoing debate
over tax cuts is the description of tax cuts as ``spending'' _ as
if tax relief were some sort of government giveaway program. Think
about it. Ever since the possibility was raised that the federal
government might be racking up gigantic budget surpluses in coming
years, the politicians and the media have been babbling about the
best way to ``spend'' all the extra money. By BILL THOMPSON. Story
has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
