   SOCIETY-GUNS (Undted) _ Authorities on aggression, violence and
culture see a pattern of particularly destructive responses to
modern stresses. But they also caution against drawing sweeping
conclusions about what deadly attacks, such as those in recent
days, reveal. By Mitchell Zuckoff. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   PBS-LISTS (Undated) _ Federal public broadcasting officials move
to end a controversy over membership lists, announcing that
stations must ban the practice of sharing them with political
fundraisers if they hope to get federal grants, starting in
October. By Peter Howe. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   INSURE-CHILDREN (Undated) _ Since the US government made $26
billion available two years ago to help states reach the goal of
covering at least 5 million uninsured children by the year 2002,
just a few more than a million have been signed up. By Dolores
Kong. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DAY-TRADING (Undated) _ John Skiersch knows what it feels like
to lose your shirt day-trading. He lost $200,000, his home and many
of his personal relationships chasing the dream of easy riches his
firm promised. By Steven Wilmsen. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   BIOPURE-IPO (Undated) _ Biopure has a disappointing IPO, raising
only $42 million, far less than the $70 million or so it initially
hoped for. By Kimberly Blanton. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   UPS-JOBS (Undated) _ Two years after a Teamsters strike nearly
crippled United Parcel Service, a dissident union group says UPS
has failed to create 10,000 new full-time jobs. By Diane E. Lewis.
550 words.
</P>
