   H.F. Lenz Company of Johnstown won a $750,000 contract from the
National Park Service in Denver Colo. for architect and engineering
services.
</P>
<P>
   Night Vision Equipment Co Inc. of Allentown won a $53,940
contract from the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for
communication, detection and coherent radiation equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Transicoil Inc. of Trooper won a $99,988 contract from Tinker
Air Forrce Base in Oklahoma for instruments and laboratory
equipment.
</P>
<P>
   ATD-American Co. of Wyncote won a $191,401 contract from the
Defense Personnel Support Center in Philadelphia, Penn., for
clothes and apparel.
</P>
<P>
   United Defense L.P. of York won a $384,000 contract from the
U.S. Army Tank Automotive and Armaments Command Acquisition Center
in Warren, Mich., for ground effeect vehicles, motor vehicles,
trailers and cycles.
</P>
<P>
   Kampi Components Co., Inc. of Bristol won a $30,761 contract
from the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for vehicular
equipment components.
</P>
<P>
   kampi Components Co. Inc. of Bristol won a $28,328 contract from
the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for pumps and
compressors.
</P>
<P>
   Schutte and Koerting Co of Bensalem won a $25,270 contract from
teh Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio for pipes, tubing, hose
and fittings.
</P>
<P>
