woman on life support was granted a temporary guardianship of his
wife Friday. He asks for the court's relief after receiving a
letter from the hospital indicating that if the brain-wave test
shows the woman dead, the hospital will not honor the temporary
restraining order that is keeping her alive right now. By RON
NISSIMOV.
</P>
<P>
   NASA-SHUTTLE (Undated ) _ NASA says the fuel leak on the shuttle
Columbia was most likely caused by a metal pin that was hurled from
the spacecraft's rocket engines. But space agency officials say the
investigation of the leak, which caused no harm, will continue. By
MARK CARREAU. (Already filed.)
</P>
