   HILLARY-CLINTON-BANKS (Washington) _ Senate Banking Committee
Chairman Phil Gramm, R-Texas, says First Lady Hillary Rodham
Clinton's bid for a U.S. Senate seat may boost prospects for
enactment of legislation that would allow banks, securities and
insurance firms to merge. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN. (Filed
Thursday.)
