   INTERNET-WINE (Washington) _ The wine industry is fighting
legislation aimed at stopping teen-agers from ordering its products
over the Internet, contending the measure will hurt small vintners
trying to make sales to adults on the Web and through mail-order
catalogues. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN. (Filed Thursday.)
</P>
