   RIVLIN-FED (Washington) _ Alice Rivlin, once told by Harvard's
public service school that women need not apply, has had
high-profile government jobs that many Harvard grads can only dream
of holding. Rivlin, who just stepped down as vice chairman of the
Federal Reserve, looks back on three decades of public service. By
JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN. (Filed Thursday.)
</P>
