School field in June. Coates, probably the NFL's best of his era at
his position, may never see his career fully acknowledged because
he has never been there to speak about it. But his words probably
couldn't add much more to this resume of five Pro Bowl selections,
five straight years of catching 60 or more passes, and the power to
fight off what is usually double coverage to haul in Drew Bledsoe's
passes. (Jim Davis/Boston Globe Photo)
