   &UR; MILK _ &LR;  The dairy industry recently made an unsuccessful
attempt to put out an ad to woo soda drinkers. The failure of the
ad that never made it past the script stage underscores the
limitations of milk marketing, especially when it comes to fighting
soda. The barriers include: opposition from networks and from the
conservative commodities boards that pay for milk ads, a small
budget relative to soda and finding the right ''creative'' to get
the message across. BY CAROL EMERT.
