<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-GA-SHOOT-RDP-NYT, which moved in
``a'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Words cannot tell the agony. Why did I? I have been dying
since October. Wake up at night so afraid, so terrified that I
couldn't be that afraid while awake. It has taken its toll. I have
come to hate this life and this system of things. I have come to
have no hope.''
</P>
<P>
   _MARK O. BARTON, in a note explaining the rampage that left 13
people, including him, dead.
</P>
</TEXT>
